## Description

Before releasing the new Recommend API client, we changed the API to support multi-query on the methods. The methods only accept arrays now.

## Usage

```ts
import algoliarecommend from '@algolia/recommend';

const recommendClient = algoliarecommend('appId', 'apiKey');

recommendClient
  .getRelatedProducts([
    {
      /* ... */
    },
  ])
  .then((response) => {
    console.log(response);
  });
```

This adds a new API client for Recommend.

## Usage

```ts
import algoliarecommend from '@algolia/recommend';

const recommendClient = algoliarecommend('appId', 'apiKey');

recommendClient
  .getRelatedProducts({
    /* ... */
  })
  .then((response) => {
    console.log(response);
  });
```

## API

### `getRelatedProducts`

Returns items from the `related-products` AI model.

### `getFrequentlyBoughtTogether`

Returns items from the `bought-together` AI model.

### `getRecommendations`

Returns items from the provided AI model (other methods are based on that one).

